---

<p align="center">
  OneCite is a powerful command-line tool and Python library designed to automate the tedious process of citation management. Feed it anything‚ÄîDOIs, paper titles, arXiv IDs, or even a mix‚Äîand get clean, accurate bibliographic entries in return.
</p>

---

## ‚ú® Features

| Feature                 | Description                                                                                             |
| ----------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| üîç **Smart Recognition**    | Fuzzy matching against multiple academic databases to find references from incomplete or inaccurate info. |
| üìö **Universal Formats**    | Input `.txt`/`.bib` ‚Üí Output **BibTeX**, **APA**, or **MLA** formats with ease.                     |
| üéØ **High-Accuracy Pipeline** | A 4-stage process (clean ‚Üí query ‚Üí validate ‚Üí format) ensures the highest quality output.             |
| ü§ñ **Auto-Completion**      | Automatically enriches entries by filling in missing data like journal, volume, pages, and authors.   |
| üéì **7+ Citation Types**    | Handles journal articles, conference papers, books, software, datasets, theses, and preprints.        |
| üß† **Intelligent Routing**  | Auto-detects content type and domain (Medical/CS/General) for optimal data retrieval.                 |
| üìÑ **Universal Identifiers**| Accepts DOI, PMID, arXiv ID, ISBN, GitHub URL, Zenodo DOI, or even plain text queries.               |
| üéõÔ∏è **Interactive Mode**    | Manually select the correct entry when multiple potential matches are found.                          |
| ‚öôÔ∏è **Custom Templates**     | A YAML-based template system provides complete control over the final output format.                  |


